manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Learn more about USB Flash Drive reserved Space Reserved Space Percentage = (Actual Capacity-User Capacity) / User Capacity Frequently Asked Questions : Why I bought 32GB USB Flash Drive, but the computer show it is about 28.98GB? Reason:The USB flash drive manufacturer take a part of the total storage capacity as reserved Space during firmware programming. There are two types of reserved space, read-intensive and higher write-intensive. Reserving space can improve performance and durability of solid, in order to help extend the life of USB Flash drive.That is why people buy 32GB USB Flash Drive, but the computer show it is about 28.98GB.
